Configuration class that allows self-referencing values

Examples:

config.configure { |c| c.set :abc, 'value' }
config.abc => 'value'

config.configure { |c| c.set 'abc.def', 'value' }
config.abc.def => 'value'

config.configure do |c|
  c.set(:abc) {'hello'}
  c.set(:def) {"#{config.abc} world!"}
end
config.def => "hello world!"

See other examples in the spec.
